dbo:abstract

Sthree Sahasam (alternate spelling: Strisahasam) (transl. Women's Allurement) is a 1951 Indian Tamil-language film, originally produced in Telugu, directed by Vedantam Raghavaiah. The film stars Akkineni Nageswara Rao and Anjali Devi. (en)
